parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, the engine failure can also cause a fire.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud knocking or banging noise
the vehicle loses power
the check engine warning light illuminates
the oil light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or dies
metal shavings are found in the oil
the engine catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of braking ability, increased risk of accidents, and potential fires.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop
unusual noises or vibrations when braking
brake fluid leaks
warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of braking ability, increased risk of accidents, and potential fires.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop
unusual noises or vibrations when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn-out brake rotors and pads can cause a loss of braking ability, increased risk of accidents, and potential damage to other brake components.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations when braking
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine makes a clicking or rattling noise
loses power
and may catch fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shifts hard
hesitates
or fails to engage
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AWD system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The AWD warning light illuminates
and the vehicle may lose traction or power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifter or transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gear shifter is difficult to operate
or the transmission slips or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall or seize, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine stalls or seizes
often without warning.
